the class must be reachable, which makes me think that `javax.swing.plaf.nimbus.NimbusLookAndFeel` should be okay in the `java.desktop` module. But what about the class initialization? If it’s a single argument, it initializes true. I want to avoid any UI issues, so I’ll just return the class without triggering initialization. My approach for `getAqua` and `getSubstance` will catch any missing classes and return null, which seems straightforward.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring Groovy MOP usage**\\n\\nI’m considering using Groovy MOP with `LookAndFeelHelper.invokeMethod('class$', ['java.lang.String'] as Object[])`. This approach seems more reflective, and I'm curious if it's the right direction. It might give me some insights into how to manage class references in a dynamic way. I want to ensure I’m leveraging the right methods effectively, so I'll keep thinking about this and see if it leads to a solution.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MoqUBIoE8xhE9c6hi8dZU5nt|fc_0ace4829bc3ec8250169fb794ad2008195949f8e340fc43e1c", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.codehaus.groovy/groovy-all/2.3.6/src/test/groovy/org_codehaus_groovy/groovy_all/LookAndFeelHelperTest.groovy", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_codehaus_groovy.groovy_all\n\nimport groovy.swing.LookAndFeelHelper\nimport javax.swing.plaf.metal.MetalLookAndFeel\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test\n\npublic class LookAndFeelHelperTest {\n    @Test\n    void resolvesOptionalLookAndFeelClassNames() {\n        String nimbusLookAndFeel = LookAndFeelHelper.getNimbusLAFName()\n        String aquaLookAndFeel = LookAndFeelHelper.getAquaLAFName()\n        String substanceLookAndFeel = LookAndFeelHelper.getSubstanceLAFName()\n\n        assert nimbusLookAndFeel == null || nimbusLookAndFeel.contains('NimbusLookAndFeel')\n        assert aquaLookAndFeel == null || aquaLookAndFeel.contains('AquaLookAndFeel')\n        assert substanceLookAndFeel == null || substanceLookAndFeel.contains('SubstanceLookAndFeel')\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void resolvesKnownClassThroughGeneratedClassHelper() {\n        Class<?> resolvedClass = LookAndFeelHelper.'class$'('javax.swing.plaf.metal.MetalLookAndFeel')\n\n        assert resolvedClass == MetalLookAndFeel\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 292, "output": 1570, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25926, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778088248882, "responseId": "resp_0ace4829bc3ec8250169fb793996288195855d2cfebb519275"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_MoqUBIoE8xhE9c6hi8dZU5nt|fc_0ace4829bc3ec8250169fb794ad2008195949f8e340fc43e1c", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1196 bytes to tests/src/org.codehaus.groovy/groovy-all/2.3.6/src/test/groovy/org_codehaus_groovy/groovy_all/LookAndFeelHelperTest.groovy"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778088269421}]}
